<title>UK: Pilkington weakens as Kleinwort downgrades.</title>
<headline>Pilkington weakens as Kleinwort downgrades.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in glassmaker Pilkington Plc nudged lower on Friday as analysts at Dresdner Kleinwort Benson cut the stock to a &quot;sell&quot; from a &quot;hold,&quot; dealers said.</p>
<p>Analysts at Kleinwort declined comment on reasons for the change in stance.</p>
<p>Pilkington shares were down 1/2p at 127 by 1018 MT in volume of 1.6 million shares. The stock has recovered from its four-year low of 109p set on May 1 but is still trading well below its 1996 high of 223-1/2p, set last March.</p>
<p>-- David Holmes, London Newsroom +44 171 542 4367</p>
